\begin_layout Standard
We can now formulate the transition matrix elements calculation for the
 special case of the 2 band model presented in section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sub:Two-Band-Model"

\end_inset

.
 When calculating 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu_{t}$
\end_inset

, all possible transitions between the involved conduction and valence subbands
 (HH or LH) have to be taken into consideration, yielding
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
\left|\mu_{\mathbf{k}}\right|^{2}=\frac{1}{2}\sum_{u_{c},\bar{u}_{c}}\sum_{u_{v},\bar{u}_{v}}\left|\left\langle u_{c}\vert\hat{\mathbf{e}}\cdot\mathbf{p}\vert u_{v}\right\rangle \left\langle F_{c}\vert F_{v}\right\rangle \right|^{2}.\label{eq:45}\end{equation}

\end_inset

The factor 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{1}{2}$
\end_inset

 compensates for the spin degeneracy.
 It is customary to express 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\mu_{\mathbf{k}}\right|$
\end_inset

 as a function of 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\mu_{0}\right|=\left\langle u_{c}\vert\hat{\mathbf{e}}\cdot\mathbf{p}\vert u_{i}\right\rangle $
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $i=x,\, y,\, z.$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\mu_{0}\right|$
\end_inset

 can be determined from measurements of the band curvature 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Chuang1995"

\end_inset

.
 By expressing the valence bands 
\begin_inset Formula $u_{v}$
\end_inset

 as linear combinations of the basis functions, the expression for 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\mu_{\mathbf{k}}\right|^{2}$
\end_inset

 can be much simplified.
 We assume the envelope function overlap integral to be unity, because of
 the moment we will be interested in is a transition between two bulk plane
 wave states.
 We find for the normalized transition strength in bulk material 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
\frac{\left|\mu_{\mathbf{k}}\right|^{2}}{\left|\mu_{0}\right|^{2}}=\left\{ \begin{array}{c}
\frac{1}{2}\left(1-\left|\hat{\mathbf{k}}\cdot\hat{\mathbf{e}}\right|^{2}\right),\,\,\,\, HH\\
\frac{1}{2}\left(\frac{1}{3}+\left|\hat{\mathbf{k}}\cdot\hat{\mathbf{e}}\right|^{2}\right),\,\,\,\, LH\end{array}\right..\label{eq:46}\end{equation}

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\mathbf{k}}$
\end_inset

